verbose_text: Adiponectin also inhibited the mRNA expression of the osteoclast associated factors RANKL, OSCAR, TRAP and Cathepsin K. Comparison between the non adiponectin group and the adiponectin group revealed that adiponectin increased the expression of AdipoR1 on the surface of osteoclast precursor cells (26.21 +/-4.27% vs. 29.86 +/-6.23%; P < 0.05) and reduced the expression of phosphorylated (p-) mTOR (7.89 +/-1.00% vs. 5.91 +/-1.26%; P < 0.05) and p-4EBP1 (26.78 +/-5.00% vs. 22.49 +/-4.24%; P < 0.05).
